org.orgName: United States Circuit Court for the District of Washington

div1.p: Received this Mittimus with the within named Prisoner, on the day of A.D. 1894, and on the same day I committed the said Prisoner to the custody of the within named jail Keeper, and left with him a certified copy of this Writ.
div1.ab: THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA. Vs. Ah Jack.
div1.p: I certify the above and foregoing to be a true copy of the Original Writ issued by me.
IN THE UNITED STATES CIRCUIT COURT, DISTRICT OF WASHINGTON, NORTHERN DIVISION.
Considering the above and foregoing petition, and the matter and things therein settled,

It is ordered that the writ prayed for issue, and that the said Jailer is whave have the body of the said Ah Jack, the petitioner named in the above and foregoing petition, before me at the United States Court in the City of Seattle, at the hour of M, on day of June, 1894
div1.ab: United States Circuit Court District of Washington Northern Division
Petition and Application of Ah Jack

ab.del: Filed 6/29 1894 IN THE U.S.DISTRICT COURT RM Hopkins Clerk By Deputy

div1.ab: Filed June 29 1894 IN THE U.S. CIRCUIT COURT. A. Reeves Ayres, Clerk. By R M Hopkins Deputy.
